600 of the 800 houses in our neighborhood flooded
    </title>

    <description>
We met with Barbara in the backyard of her home, still in the midst of
repairs, eight months after the floods from Hurricane Harvey left a
trail of destruction through Houston, Texas.  She shared a few of the
never-ending list of challenges and "flood brain" weariness in trying
to recover from an event like this, from rescuing your cat, to chasing
down your mail, to selecting new door knobs.
